-- 
European Banks May Introduce Regional Credit Cards, FTD Reports

-- B y   N i k l a s   M a g n u s s o n
-- 
2011-07-06T06:47:24Z

-- http://www.bloomberg.com/news/2011-07-06/european-banks-may-introduce-regional-credit-cards-ftd-reports.html
European banks will make a decision
later this year on whether to introduce a European credit card
to challenge the payment networks of  MasterCard Inc. (MA)  and  Visa
Inc. (V) , the  Financial Times Deutschland  reported, citing project
officials.  About 24 banks from seven countries, including  Germany ,
 France , the U.K. and  Spain , are involved in the plan, the
newspaper said, citing Georges Pauget, the head of the project
and former chief executive officer of  Credit Agricole SA. (ACA)   To contact the reporter on this story:
Niklas Magnusson in Hamburg at 
